                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d311">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-07-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Loomis states that Mr. Griscom reports that the crew of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Knight Commander</hi> testify that the vessel was sunk for
                    want of coal to proceed to Vladivostok, and that the United States Government
                    considers that the sinking of the vessel was not justified by the bare fact that
                    there was contraband of war aboard. Cites as authorities Note to Dana’s Wheaton,
                    eighth edition, page 485, and Hall, Twiss, and Lawrence.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
